  {
    "id": 292, "title": "Minimum Taps to Water Garden", "difficulty": "Medium", "tags": ["Greedy", "DP", "Array"],
    "description": "## Minimum Taps to Water a Garden\n\nA garden of length `n` runs from `0` to `n`. Tap `i` at position `i` covers `[i-ranges[i], i+ranges[i]]`. Find the minimum number of taps to water the entire garden, or `-1` if impossible.\n\n**Input:** Line 1: `n`. Line 2: `n+1` integers (ranges).\n\n**Output:** Minimum taps, or `-1`.\n\n**Constraints:** `1 ≤ n ≤ 10^4`, `0 ≤ ranges[i] ≤ 100`",
    "examples": [{"input": "5\n3 4 1 1 0 0", "output": "1", "explanation": "Tap 1 covers [0,5]"}, {"input": "3\n0 0 0 0", "output": "-1"}],
    "testCases": [{"input": "5\n3 4 1 1 0 0", "expected": "1"}, {"input": "3\n0 0 0 0", "expected": "-1"}, {"input": "7\n1 2 1 0 2 1 0 1", "expected": "3"}, {"input": "1\n0 1", "expected": "1"}, {"input": "4\n0 0 0 0 4", "expected": "1"}],
    "template": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n    int n; cin >> n;\n    vector<int> ranges(n+1);\n    for(int i=0;i<=n;i++) cin>>ranges[i];\n    // Convert to jump game: maxReach[i] = farthest right coverage starting from i\n    vector<int> maxR(n+1, 0);\n    for(int i=0;i<=n;i++) {\n        int l=max(0,i-ranges[i]), r=min(n,i+ranges[i]);\n        maxR[l]=max(maxR[l], r);\n    }\n    // Greedy jump: current reach, next reach, taps used\n    \n    return 0;\n}"
  },
